# DMS frontend module rules

- Read `contracts.ts` before editing this module.
- Use governed `/api/v2/dms/` envelopes and `ENDPOINTS`; never hardcode API paths.
- File content enters through browser `File` + multipart requests only. Storage keys,
  MIME detection, measured size, checksums, tenant IDs, and audit identity are server-owned.
- All collection/detail controls fail closed against typed `allowed_actions` projections.
- Existing share tokens never enter query caches or read contracts; `share_url` is handled
  only in the one-time creation result.
- Document content changes create immutable versions. Metadata editing must carry
  `expected_updated_at` and surface conflicts instead of overwriting newer state.
- Keep initial/loading, background refresh, empty/filtered-empty, denied, not-found,
  validation, dependency-failure, retry, and pending-mutation states explicit.
- Keep pages in the module-owned tenant route registry and preserve the sidebar parent.
- Do not add `any`, unchecked `unknown` casts, legacy resource aliases, PUT mutations,
  raw principal UUID fields, or plaintext token/storage fields.
- Run scoped ESLint and DMS Vitest tests after every change; the repository gates also
  require the full frontend typecheck, lint, test, and build suites.
